The Employment Cycle: a smarter way to think about HR

At Bare Bones Consulting, we consider HR from your perspective. We understand you want simplicity, results and value for money solutions to your HR challenges.

Our approach is based on the Employment Cycle: a simple, no nonsense concept comprising only 4 elements. When you incorporate each element into a working HR function, you’ll see benefits across the board:

  • access to a deeper candidate pool
  • recruit the right person first time
  • retain your top performers
  • less employee conflicts and grievances
  • improved productivity, quality and revenue
  • reduced HR risk

Bare Bones’ Employment Cycle approach is unique. And it saves you time, money and rework. Contact us now for a complimentary chat…it might be the smartest investment you ever make!

The Way We Work

Many HR processes run silently in the background of your business. They’re the backbone of your employee management function; providing structure to your most important business records and peace of mind for you.

But getting this right can take up a lot of your time, particularly when you’re not a Human Resources expert. With the right HR processes in place and a little coaching from us you have the time to focus on the real reasons you got into business... and really succeed! Getting started couldn’t be easier.

We Chat

Our process starts with a simple conversation. Tell us what you need and we’ll do the rest: no obligation, no commitment and no cost for our initial consultation.

We Review

We consider what HR paperwork, people and systems you have in place, pinpoint specific areas of concern and provide you a report on our findings.

We Prioritise

We work with you to define your current priorities, identify where you’re heading in the future and show you what’s possible.

We Customise

We look for perfect fit… and that means perfect for your business. Our solutions are tailored to you – meeting your needs and your budget.

We Act

We roll up our sleeves and, alongside you and your team, commence implementation.
